.TH ARF 1 "November 2025" "ARF 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
arf \- FLOSSI0ULLK Agent Runtime Framework CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B arf
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B arf
is a unified command-line interface for all ARF (Agent Runtime Framework) operations.
It provides tools for conversation memory management, swarm intelligence, ontology operations,
and performance benchmarking.

The CLI follows Unix philosophy: composable commands, pipeable output, and JSON mode for scripting.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress output except errors
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Show help message and exit

.SH COMMANDS
.SS memory
Conversation memory operations
.TP
.B arf memory transmit \fICONTENT\fR
Transmit understanding to conversation memory
.TP
.B arf memory recall \fIQUERY\fR
Recall understandings from memory
.TP
.B arf memory compose
Compose memories from multiple agents
.TP
.B arf memory stats
Show memory statistics
.TP
.B arf memory export
Export agent memory for composition

.SS swarm
Pony swarm operations using Recursive Self-Aggregation (RSA)
.TP
.B arf swarm query \fIQUESTION\fR
Query the pony swarm
.TP
.B arf swarm info
Show swarm configuration and capabilities

.SS ontology
Ontology validation and inference operations
.TP
.B arf ontology validate \fITRIPLE\fR
Validate a knowledge triple
.TP
.B arf ontology infer \fITRIPLE\fR
Perform inference on a triple
.TP
.B arf ontology list-predicates
List all known predicates
.TP
.B arf ontology info
Show ontology information

.SS benchmark
Benchmarking operations for performance testing
.TP
.B arf benchmark run
Run benchmark suite
.TP
.B arf benchmark list-suites
List available benchmark suites

.SH COMMON OPTIONS
Many commands support these common options:
.TP
.BR \-\-json
Output as JSON for scripting (all commands)
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-agent " " \fIAGENT_ID\fR
Specify agent ID (memory commands)
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-backend " " \fIBACKEND\fR
Specify backend: file or holochain (memory commands)

.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Memory Operations
.TP
Transmit understanding:
.B arf memory transmit "GPT-4 is a large language model"
.TP
Recall with specific agent:
.B arf memory recall "LLM" \-\-agent alice
.TP
Export memory as JSON:
.B arf memory export \-\-agent alice \-\-output alice.json
.TP
Compose memories:
.B arf memory compose \-\-agent main \-\-with alice \-\-with bob

.SS Swarm Operations
.TP
Query the swarm:
.B arf swarm query "What is 47 * 89?"
.TP
Custom parameters:
.B arf swarm query "Explain recursion" \-\-ponies 6 \-\-iterations 4

.SS Ontology Operations
.TP
Validate a triple:
.B arf ontology validate "(GPT-4, is_a, LLM)"
.TP
List predicates as JSON:
.B arf ontology list-predicates \-\-json | jq '.predicates[]'

.SS Benchmarking
.TP
Run memory benchmark:
.B arf benchmark run \-\-suite memory \-\-iterations 10
.TP
Run all benchmarks:
.B arf benchmark run \-\-suite all \-\-json

.SH JSON OUTPUT
All commands support
.B \-\-json
flag for machine-readable output. This enables:
.TP
\(bu Scripting and automation
.TP
\(bu Pipeline composition with jq and other tools
.TP
\(bu Integration with other systems
.PP
Example:
.RS
.B arf memory recall "test" \-\-json | jq '.results[0].content'
.RE

